<%= render 'admin/shared/import_form',
           preview_path: preview_admin_user_imports_path,
           cancel_path: admin_users_path,
           cancel_text: "Back to Users",
           columns_description: "Name | Student ID (optional) | Email (optional)",
           placeholder_text: "Name\tStudent ID\tEmail\nFinbar the Viking\ts1234567\tfinbar@viking.se\nErik Bloodaxe\t\terik@norse.no" do %>
  <p>The import process matches each row against existing users in the following order:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Student/Associate ID match:</strong> If a user with the same ID exists, they will be linked</li>
    <li><strong>Email match:</strong> If a user with the same email exists, they will be linked</li>
    <li><strong>Name match:</strong> If an <em>active</em> user with the same last name and similar first name exists, you'll be asked to confirm</li>
    <li><strong>No match:</strong> A new user account will be created</li>
  </ol>
  <p class="mb-0 text-muted">
    <strong>Note:</strong> If a student ID is provided but no email, the email will be auto-generated as <span class="font-monospace">&lt;student_id&gt;@ed.ac.uk</span>.
    This import does <strong>not</strong> activate membership - use the Membership Import for that.
  </p>
<% end %>
